li.p:
The prescribed order of elements in the affected parameter is retained:
                label; usage; constraint; guideline;
                value or select (a choice); and link.

section.p:
A control can be altered by an alter directive on a control. The
            @control-id flag on the alter indicates the control to which the
          alteration is applied.

Additionally, with an explicit binding given by a @ref-id,
                @position may have any of the values starting,
                ending, before and after.
